Properties of Object oriented Programming

1 - Inheritance
2 - Polymorphism
3 - Encapsulation
4 - Abstraction

INHERITANCE : One class inherits the properties of other class the class which inherits the
properties is called the derived / child / subclass and the class from which it is derived
is called Derived / Parent / super class .


Types of Inheritance :
1 - Single Inheritance
2 - Multilevel Inheritance
3 - Multiple Inheritance - Creating a single class with multiple superclasses / Parent class
4 - Hierarchical Inheritance - Many child classes are derived with one parent class
5 - Hybrid Inheritance